 Abidemi Rufai has now been slammed with 9 Counts Of Wire Fraud, 5 Counts Of Aggravated Identity Theft & Conspiracy following his arrest. This was announced by Acting U.S. Attorney, Tessa M. Gorman, who said that Rufai has now been indicted for conspiracy, wire fraud, and aggravated identity theft. According to reports, Rufai was believed to have put up a scheme to steal over $350,000 in unemployment benefits from the Washington State Employment Security Department, among many other crimes.